Python wrapper over sms.sluzba.cz HTTP API
----------------
Simple wrapper for sending SMS messages via paid sms.sluzba.cz SMS gateway.


In 'Lite' version of API, which is implemented by SmsApiLite class,
it is possible only to send text with minimal feedback.
SmsApiLite acts as a wrapper over content of HTTP request and response.
See SMS_Gate_API_LITE_20.pdf for request/response description.

Example of using SmsApiLite class:
from smssluzbacz import SmsApiLite, SmsApiException

api = SmsApiLite('username', 'password')
api.send('+420773885311', 'OHAI!')

If you have sms.sluzba.cz account, you can quickly test using 'example.py' script.

$ ./example.py username password +420773885311 OHAI
2011-07-05 19:36:53,072	DEBUG	Initiated SmsApiLite for user: username
2011-07-05 19:36:53,072	INFO	Sending SMS to number: +420773885311, message text: OHAI
2011-07-05 19:36:53,073	DEBUG	Use HTTPS: True, Use HTTP POST: True, API URL: https://smsgateapi.sluzba.cz/apilite20/sms
2011-07-05 19:36:53,966	DEBUG	Response received: 200 Zprava byla uspesne odeslana
2011-07-05 19:36:53,966	INFO	SMS sent successfully

In case of something goes wrong, SmsApiException is raised.

$ ./example.py username password InvalidPhoneNumber OHAI
2011-07-05 19:38:46,265	DEBUG	Initiated SmsApiLite for user: username
2011-07-05 19:38:46,266	INFO	Sending SMS to number: InvalidPhoneNumber, message text: OHAI
2011-07-05 19:38:46,266	DEBUG	Use HTTPS: True, Use HTTP POST: True, API URL: https://smsgateapi.sluzba.cz/apilite20/sms
2011-07-05 19:38:46,548	DEBUG	Response received: 400;1 Chybne telefonni cislo InvalidPhoneNumber
2011-07-05 19:38:46,549	ERROR	SMS API error occured: 400;1 Chybne telefonni cislo InvalidPhoneNumber
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "./example.py", line 23, in <module>
    main()
    ..............
    raise SmsApiException(response) 
smssluzbacz.SmsApiException


Notes: There is restriction on sms.sluzba.cz that will block you account after
several invalid login attempts.

Requirements
------------
Python, urllib

Tested on:
Python 2.7.1+ [GCC 4.5.2] on linux2

